PSTN service provides three methods to promote connectivity.\nUse PSTN solely or in combination with other services.

1. Keep app running in the background: 
If Keep app running in the background is enabled, a notification will be shown on the notification bar for testing purposes.
The feature allows the app to run in the background for a long time (depending on different brands) 


2. Audio call: 
SIP calls are automatically switched to audio calls if failed.
If you start an audio call by clicking Auido Call and fails to get connected after 15 seconds, you are switched to SIP calling. The trigger condition can be customized.


3. SMS notification:
The feature can notify the called parity of call requests. Users can open the app can handle the requests.
If an audio or video call is connecting for 30 seconds and fails, an SMS notification will be delivered.
